		"description": "<p>Your divinely-granted and academically-studied magic are starting to merge together, allowing you to do some things that more conventional spellcasters cannot. You gain the following benefits:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Your Intelligence or Wisdom score increases by 1, to a maximum of 20.</li>\n<li>When you cast a wizard spell that deals damage, you can spend a use of @UUID[Compendium.a5e.a5e-class-features.Item.s4iiatrup3e3virw]{Channel Divinity} to change the damage type as follows:\n<ul>\n<li>Fire or lightning damage becomes radiant damage.</li>\n<li>Cold or poison damage becomes necrotic damage.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>When you use @UUID[Compendium.a5e.a5e-class-features.Item.iqlgotutphoratct]{Arcane Recovery}, you regain hit points as if you had expended a cleric hit die. This does not consume a hit die. In addition, you can also swap out a number of prepared spells equal to half your proficiency bonus from your cleric list for different spells from your cleric list and a number of prepared spells equal to half your proficiency bonus from your wizard list for different spells from your wizard list.</li>\n</ul>",
